## Overview

This document describes the architecture and Terraform-managed configuration of the AWS Organization management account. The management account is the root of the AWS Organization and is responsible for account management, delegated admin registration, trusted access enablement, Service Control Policies (SCPs), and organizational unit (OU) structure. All management account infrastructure is now controlled via Terraform and deployed through a GitHub Actions CI/CD pipeline using OIDC federation.

---

## Management Account Responsibilities

The management account is the only account in the organization that can perform the following actions:

- Create and manage organizational units (OUs)
- Invite or create member accounts
- Register and deregister delegated administrators for AWS services
- Enable and disable trusted access for AWS service principals
- Create, attach, and manage Service Control Policies (SCPs)
- Manage the organization's root-level settings

**Important:** SCPs do not apply to the management account itself. The management account always retains full permissions regardless of any SCP attached to the organization root or any OU.

---

## Organizational Unit Structure

The OU hierarchy organizes accounts by function and controls which SCPs apply to each group of accounts.

| OU | Purpose | Accounts | SCPs Applied |
|---|---|---|---|
| Root | Organization root | Management account | FullAWSAccess (default) |
| Security OU | Centralized security tooling | Security account | FullAWSAccess, deny-org-nonadmin (with exception) |
| [Workload OU] | Application workloads | Member accounts | FullAWSAccess, deny-org-nonadmin |
| [Sandbox OU] | Development and testing | Sandbox accounts | [As applicable] |

