## Trusted Access

Trusted access must be enabled at the Organization level for each service that uses delegated admin or org-wide features. Delegation registration alone is not sufficient — both delegation and trusted access are required. This is managed via Terraform using `aws_organizations_organization` resource features or explicit `aws_organizations_service_access` resources.

### Enabled Service Principals

| Service Principal | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `config.amazonaws.com` | Allows Config to operate org-wide (aggregator, org rules) |
| `config-multiaccountsetup.amazonaws.com` | Allows Config multi-account setup features |
| `guardduty.amazonaws.com` | Allows GuardDuty org-wide threat detection |
| `securityhub.amazonaws.com` | Allows Security Hub org-wide finding aggregation |

**Verification CLI command:**
```bash
aws organizations list-aws-service-access-for-organization
```

All four service principals must appear in the output. If any are missing, the corresponding delegated admin features will fail in the security account even though delegation is registered.

