## Service Control Policies (SCPs)

SCPs are managed via Terraform and applied to OUs to enforce organization-wide guardrails. The management account is exempt from all SCPs.

### FullAWSAccess (Default)

The default AWS-managed SCP that allows all actions. Attached to the organization root and inherited by all OUs.

```json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": "*",
      "Resource": "*"
    }
  ]
}
```

### deny-org-nonadmin

A custom SCP that prevents member accounts from making Organizations API calls. This blocks actions like listing accounts, describing the organization, or modifying org settings from non-admin accounts.

```json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Deny",
      "Action": "organizations:*",
      "Resource": "*",
      "Condition": {
        "StringNotEquals": {
          "aws:PrincipalAccount": "<security-account-id>"
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

**Target:** Applied to the parent OU that contains the security account and workload accounts.

**Security account exception:** The condition `StringNotEquals` on `aws:PrincipalAccount` exempts the security account from this deny. This is required because delegated admin services (Config, GuardDuty, Security Hub) need to call Organizations APIs such as `organizations:ListDelegatedAdministrators` and `organizations:ListAccounts` from the security account.

**Why this matters:** Without this exception, the security account will receive `OrganizationAccessDeniedException` errors when creating Config aggregators, deploying organization conformance packs, or performing other delegated admin operations — even though the IAM role has the correct permissions. SCPs are evaluated before IAM policies, and an SCP deny overrides any IAM allow.

**Terraform resource example:**
```hcl
resource "aws_organizations_policy" "deny_org_nonadmin" {
  name        = "deny-org-nonadmin"
  description = "Deny organizations API access except for security account"
  type        = "SERVICE_CONTROL_POLICY"
  content     = jsonencode({
    Version = "2012-10-17"
    Statement = [
      {
        Effect    = "Deny"
        Action    = "organizations:*"
        Resource  = "*"
        Condition = {
          StringNotEquals = {
            "aws:PrincipalAccount" = var.security_account_id
          }
        }
      }
    ]
  })
}

resource "aws_organizations_policy_attachment" "deny_org_nonadmin" {
  policy_id = aws_organizations_policy.deny_org_nonadmin.id
  target_id = var.target_ou_id
}
```

