## Terraform State and Repository Structure

| Component | Repository / Workspace | AWS Account Target |
|---|---|---|
| Org management (OUs, SCPs, delegation, trusted access) | [repo/path] | Management account |
| Security tooling (Config, GuardDuty, Security Hub, IAM roles) | [repo/path] | Security account |

*Update the table above with your actual repository paths and workspace names.*

**Order of operations for initial deployment:**

1. Deploy management account Terraform first — this creates the OUs, SCPs, delegated admin registrations, and trusted access.
2. Deploy security account Terraform second — this creates the Config aggregator, conformance packs, GuardDuty configuration, Security Hub settings, and IAM roles.

If the security account Terraform is applied before the management account Terraform has completed delegation and trusted access setup, Config aggregator creation and other delegated admin operations will fail.

